        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Hiroya Nozaki",
          "email": "nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com",
          "date": "2015-05-28 06:02:34.000000000",
          "tz": 540
        },
        "subject": "LU-6625 llite: symlink() sets wrong errno, ENOENT",
        "message": "LU-6625 llite: symlink() sets wrong errno, ENOENT\n\nAccording to the online-manual symlink() should set errno EEXIST when\nspecified link-path already exists. but it actually sets ENOENT when\nthe last ward of the link path is \"/\".\n\nThis patch modifies a if-statement in ll_lookup_nd for client to look\nup MDS properly and for symlink() to set errno EEXIST\n\nSigned-off-by: Hiroya Nozaki <nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com>\nChange-Id: Iec603139d2ebebea339f185a481bd8d2a4074deb\n"
      },
